SIMPLE: drawbore
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drawbore
<hw>Draw"bore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Joinery)</fld>
<def>A hole bored through a tenon nearer to the shoulder than the holes
through the cheeks are to the edge or abutment against which the
shoulder is to rest, so that a pin or bolt, when driven into it, will
draw these parts together.</def> <rj><au>Weale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawbore</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Drawbore
<hw>Draw"bore`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make a
drawbore in; <as>as, to <ex>drawbore</ex> a tenon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To enlarge the bore of a gun barrel by drawing,
instead of thrusting, a revolving tool through it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drawboy</ent>⟦br⟧
